---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ExportImport from '../components/ExportImport';
---

<Layout title="About — The AI Course">
  <div class="max-w-2xl py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">About this course</h1>

    <div class="prose mt-6">
      <p>
        The AI Course merges three <a href="https://roadmap.sh">roadmap.sh</a> roadmaps —
        <a href="https://roadmap.sh/ai-engineer">AI Engineer</a>,
        <a href="https://roadmap.sh/ai-agents">AI Agents</a>, and
        <a href="https://roadmap.sh/prompt-engineering">Prompt Engineering</a> —
        into one deduplicated, logically-ordered curriculum. Prerequisites come first, and topics that
        appear on several roadmaps appear here exactly once.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site doesn't try to teach every concept itself. Each topic gives you a short, original
        overview — what it is, why it matters, how you'll use it — and then points you at the best
        external resources to actually learn it. Check off resources as you go and mark topics complete
        to track your progress through the course.
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Credits &amp; data</h2>
      <p>
        The course structure (topic list and resource links) is adapted from the
        <a href="https://github.com/kamranahmedse/developer-roadmap">roadmap.sh open-source repository</a>
        by Kamran Ahmed and contributors — thank you for an amazing resource. All topic overviews on this
        site are original writing; no roadmap.sh content is republished here. Linked articles and videos
        belong to their respective authors.
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        There is no backend, no account, and no tracking. Everything — including your course progress —
        lives in your browser's localStorage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <ExportImport client:visible />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
